# NixOS flake conventions

## Layout

- `hosts/<name>/` — thin host: hardware, boot, graphics; prefer empty `host.nix`
- `nixos/modules/` — system modules (options + `mkIf`), imported via `default.nix`
- `nixos/profiles/` — role composition (`common.nix`, `desktop.nix` set enables)
- `linux-app/` — home-manager: `apps/`, `browsers/`, `cli/`, `shell/`, `desktop/`
- Home Manager is **only** as a NixOS module (`nh os switch`), no standalone `homeConfigurations`

## Patterns

- Shared toolchain → `nixos/modules/devtools.nix` (not per-host copies)
- Host-specific services → `mkEnableOption` / default off; turn on in profile or host
- Heavy HM apps → own file under `linux-app/apps/` with local `enable = true/false` + `lib.mkIf`
- Packages: prefer domain modules over growing `linux-app/packages.nix`
- Unfree/insecure: only in `nixos/modules/nix.nix`; HM uses `home-manager.useGlobalPkgs = true`
- Shells: fish is default; zsh optional via HM — do not put bare `zsh` in `packages.nix`
- Apply changes with `nh os switch ./` (alias `sw`), not `nh home switch`

## Anti-patterns

- Hardcoded `/nix/store/...` paths in app configs (e.g. KiCad lib tables)
- Copying KiCad libs into `~/kicad` (wrapper already sets `KICAD9_*`)
- Duplicating toolchain lists in `hosts/*/host.nix`
- Impure `wget` in activation when a FOD/`fetchurl` + hash exists
- Setting `nixpkgs.config.*` inside HM modules when `useGlobalPkgs` is on
